"3:165:5" : {s: 3, a: 165, w: 5, r: "صوب", t: "أَصَبْتُم", l: "أَصَابَ", lc: 64, tl: "aṣabtum", lb: "পতিত হওয়া, আক্রমন করা",e: "you (had) struck (them)", b: "তোমরা আক্রান্ত করেছ", i: "kamu telah menimpakan", f: 1, rm: "to pour forth, hit the mark, come down. asaaba - to overtake, happen to, befall, fall upon, will, affect injuriously, meet with, send down, pour down upon, afflict or punish, intend, desire. sawaabun - that which is right, straight forward course, rightness. musiibun - that which happens. musiibatun - calamity.", ag: "فعل ماض صيغة ٤ وضمير متصل ", eg: "Verb Perfect 4th form and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "PERF", qual: "(IV)", deg: "2", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَصَابَ،مُصِيبَةٌۭ"},
"3:165:6" : {s: 3, a: 165, w: 6, r: "مثل", t: "مِّثْلَيْهَا", l: "مِثْل", lc: 75, tl: "mith'layhā", lb: "তুলনা, মতো",e: "twice of it", b: "তার দ্বিগুণ", i: "dua kali serupanya (musibah)", f: 1, rm: "Stand erect, mutilate or castrate (namely a sheep or goat), to set up a thing, affect to be like or to imitate a thing, apply a proverb, apply a thing proverbially, be nearly in a sound or healthy state, near to convalescence, obey/follow a command or order, to resemble, be of likeness or equivalent.", ag: "أسم منصوب وضمير متصل ", eg: "Noun Accusative case and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACC", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "D", mood: "", lu: "مَثَلُ،مِثْلُ"},
"3:165:7" : {s: 3, a: 165, w: 7, r: "قول", t: "قُلْتُمْ", l: "قَالَ", lc: 1618, tl: "qul'tum", lb: "কথা বলা",e: "you said", b: "তোমরা বলেছিলে", i: "kamu berkata", f: 7, rm: "to say/speak, to call, to be named, word/speech, utterance, a thing said, greeting, discourse, one who says/speaks. To inspire/transmit/relate/answer/think/profess, emit an opinion on, indicate a state or condition or circumstance. qailun - speaker, indicator.", ag: "فعل ماض وضمير متصل ", eg: "Verb Perfect and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "PERF", qual: "", deg: "2", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "قَالَ،قَآئِلٌۭ،قَوْلٌۭ"},
"3:165:8" : {s: 3, a: 165, w: 8, r: "اني", t: "أَنَّىٰ", l: "أَنَّىٰ", lc: 28, tl: "annā", lb: "কোথায়",e: "From where", b: "যেভাবে", i: "bagaimana", f: 15, rm: "Its time came; or it was, or became, or drew, near; It (a thing) was, or became, behind, or after, its time; it, or he, (a man) was, or became, behind, backward, or late; it, or he, delayed, or held back. He postponed it, put it off, deferred it, delayed it, retarded it, withheld it, impeded it; An hour, or a short portion, or a time, or an indefinite time; any period of time; the utmost point, reach or degree; A thing of which the time has come, or drawn near: and which has come, or attained, to its time; to its full, or final, time or state; to maturity, or ripeness; signifies Whence? (being an interrogative respecting the direction, or quarter, from which a thing is) and whence (used to denote a condition); Where? and where (used to denote a condition and as one of the adverbial nouns used to denote a condition), whence-so-ever; wherever (from whatever direction or quarter): when; how; however.", ag: "حرف استفهام ", eg: "Interogative particle ", tag: "INTG", pos: "INTG", att: "", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "", num: "", mood: "", lu: "أَنَّىٰ"},
